---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Security Metrics: Measuring Your Program | Sheepdog" description="Track security program effectiveness with meaningful metrics. Learn what to measure and how to demonstrate security ROI." showMatrix={true}>
  <section>
    <h1>Security Metrics: Measuring Your Program</h1>
    <p class="lead">If you can't measure it, you can't improve it. Security metrics show whether your controls work, where to invest, and what ROI you're getting. Here's what to measure.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why Security Metrics Matter</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Demonstrate program effectiveness to leadership</li>
      <li>Identify areas needing improvement</li>
      <li>Show ROI on security investments</li>
      <li>Track progress over time</li>
      <li>Validate that controls actually work</li>
      <li>Identify emerging threats or trends</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Categories of Security Metrics</h2>
    
    <h3>Vulnerability Management Metrics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Total vulnerabilities found vs fixed</li>
      <li>Mean time to remediation (MTTR)</li>
      <li>Critical vulnerabilities still open</li>
      <li>Percentage of systems with current patches</li>
      <li>Vulnerability severity distribution</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Incident Response Metrics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Number of incidents (trending)</li>
      <li>Mean time to detect (MTTD)</li>
      <li>Mean time to respond (MTTR)</li>
      <li>Mean time to resolve (MTTR)</li>
      <li>Incident severity distribution</li>
      <li>Incidents detected internally vs externally</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Access Control Metrics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Percentage of users with MFA enabled</li>
      <li>Average number of privileged accounts per user</li>
      <li>Access reviews completed on schedule</li>
      <li>Failed authentication attempts (trend)</li>
      <li>Unusual access patterns detected</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Data Protection Metrics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Percentage of sensitive data encrypted</li>
      <li>Percentage of systems with disk encryption</li>
      <li>Sensitive data discovery results</li>
      <li>Data loss prevention incidents</li>
      <li>Unintended data exposures discovered</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Compliance Metrics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Audit findings (count and severity)</li>
      <li>Controls assessed vs controls total</li>
      <li>Policy compliance percentage</li>
      <li>Regulatory requirement compliance</li>
      <li>Security assessment completion rate</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Awareness & Training Metrics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Security training completion rate</li>
      <li>Phishing simulation click rate</li>
      <li>Phishing report rate</li>
      <li>Security awareness test scores</li>
      <li>Incident attribution to human error</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Asset Management Metrics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Total assets (hardware, software, cloud)</li>
      <li>Assets with current inventory data</li>
      <li>Shadow IT discoveries</li>
      <li>Unsupported or outdated technology</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Leading vs Lagging Indicators</h2>
    
    <h3>Leading Indicators (Predictive)</h3>
    <p>Show if you're building security for the future:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Patch installation rate</li>
      <li>Configuration compliance</li>
      <li>Training completion rate</li>
      <li>Security assessments completed</li>
      <li>Controls implemented</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Lagging Indicators (Reactive)</h3>
    <p>Show what already happened:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Incidents detected</li>
      <li>Breaches that occurred</li>
      <li>Audit findings</li>
      <li>Regulatory violations</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Best approach: Use leading indicators to prevent problems, lagging indicators to track results.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Setting Targets</h2>
    
    <h3>Establish Baselines</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Where are you today?</li>
      <li>Measure current state honestly</li>
      <li>Identify gaps vs best practice</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Set Realistic Goals</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Goal: 95% patch compliance (not 100%)</li>
      <li>Goal: MFA on 100% of remote access (realistic)</li>
      <li>Goal: Reduce MTTD from 200 days to 30 days</li>
      <li>Goals should be achievable but ambitious</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Roadmap</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Year 1: Basic hygiene (patching, MFA)</li>
      <li>Year 2: Detection and response (monitoring, alerting)</li>
      <li>Year 3: Advanced analytics (AI/ML, behavior analytics)</li>
      <li>Continuous improvement thereafter</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Demonstrating ROI</h2>
    
    <h3>Cost Avoidance</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Breach prevented = millions saved</li>
      <li>Incidents resolved faster = less downtime</li>
      <li>Compliance passed = avoided fines</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Efficiency Gains</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Automation reduces manual work</li>
      <li>Better monitoring reduces incident resolution time</li>
      <li>Patching automation reduces manpower</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example ROI Calculation</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Security tool investment: $100,000/year</li>
      <li>Incident prevented: $5 million cost</li>
      <li>Time saved in security work: $50,000/year</li>
      <li>ROI: ($5,000,000 + $50,000 - $100,000) / $100,000 = 4,900% ROI</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Reporting Security Metrics</h2>
    
    <h3>For Executive Leadership</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>High-level trends and business impact</li>
      <li>Key metrics dashboard</li>
      <li>Quarterly or annual reporting</li>
      <li>ROI and budget justification</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>For Security Team</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Detailed metrics and trends</li>
      <li>Specific control effectiveness</li>
      <li>Actionable findings and recommendations</li>
      <li>Monthly or weekly reporting</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>For Auditors/Regulators</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Compliance-specific metrics</li>
      <li>Control testing evidence</li>
      <li>Audit findings and remediation</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tools for Security Metrics</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SIEM:</strong> Splunk, Sumo Logic, Elastic collect security logs for analysis</li>
      <li><strong>GRC Platforms:</strong> ServiceNow, LogicGate, Archer track compliance and controls</li>
      <li><strong>Dashboards:</strong> Grafana, Tableau visualize metrics</li>
      <li><strong>Vulnerability tools:</strong> Qualys, Tenable track vulnerability metrics</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Build Your Metrics Program</h2>
    <p>Sheepdog Cyber Defense helps organizations establish security metrics and demonstrate program effectiveness.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Establish Your Metrics</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

